    <p>{`##Making Changes to Schedules
Once an on-call schedule is exported into Google Calendar, Google Calendar will `}<strong parentName="p">{`automatically`}</strong>{` update when you make a change to the on-call schedule in the web application. Therefore, once an on-call schedule has been exported, you will not need to edit it when you make changes to the schedule in PagerDuty.
